- "under the watchful eye" refers to the user having access to the financial instrument (user_access table);
- "market pulse" refers to the volume-weighted average price of the financial instrument;
- "higher than a subtle whisper" refers to the average volume-weighted average price greater than 0.69, which is a relatively low threshold.

- High average trading volumes may indicate popular or highly liquid financial instruments; 
- The year 2019 might be significant due to market trends or economic events during that time; 
- Average trading volume thresholds like 1,000,000 can be used to filter out less liquid instruments.

sql:
SELECT quarter_name
FROM reporting_quarters
WHERE year = 2019;
